article.headline: Ohio 97, Rhode Island 69
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Leon Williams scored 19 points and had 15 rebounds as Ohio defeated Rhode Island 97-69 Wednesday night. Ohio (8-3) led the entire game, and shot 60 percent from the field in the first half to build up a 55-30 halftime lead. Five Bobcats scored double-digits. The Bobcats' largest lead came with 9:54 left to play, when Stephen King made two foul shots to put Ohio ahead 83-46. King finished with 19 points and went 5-of-6 on 3-pointers. Darrell Harris and Jimmy Baron each scored 15 points for Rhode Island (7-6). Keith Cothran added 12 for the Rams. The Bobcats' Bubba Walther scored 17 points and Whitney Davis had 16. Jerome Tillman added 12 points for Ohio.
